      "title": "Senior Web Developer",
      "description": "<p><strong>Shape the future of the sports and fitness industry</strong></p>\n<p>Lenus eHealth helps fitness professionals build a strong and sustainable business by offering them an all-in-one platform for online coaching together with advisory on business development, marketing and personal branding. The digital product offering includes a full-suite CRM solution for personal trainers to manage their clients, as well as coach-branded web and mobile apps for end-users to receive programmes for meals and workouts, track progress over time and communicate with the coach.</p>\n<p>Founded in 2016, Lenus eHealth are currently the market leaders in Denmark and Sweden and are at a low start to take over new countries. Proud to have already helped people lose over 100 000 kg, they are confident that this number will grow exponentially following an international expansion.</p>\n<p><strong>The tech stack you'll meet</strong></p>\n<p>React, Node.JS, GraphQL, PostgreSQL, TypeScript, ReasonML, React Native (Expo - Managed &amp; Bare Workflow), React Native Web and ReasonReact.</p>\n<p><strong>Help move a market-leading product forward</strong></p>\n<p>Lenus is looking for a Senior Web Developer who loves to code and who has a product-oriented focus. In return, you will have a great influence on the code written and you will ensure that good software engineering practices are adopted and followed: design, testing, documentation, deployment, and operations. You will be in close cooperation with the Tech Lead, support the delivery lifecycle and help ensure that immediate issues are solved quickly and efficiently.</p>\n<p>As a Senior Web Developer, your mission will be to help move Lenus’ product efforts forward by either participating in or leading their product development projects. You will own key components within the platform: In this case, “owning\" means envisioning, designing, creating, building, and supporting.</p>\n<p>Furthermore, Lenus envisions that you will join and lead discussions around different platform initiatives and occasionally take charge of troubleshooting and maintaining high quality and low bug count in their core products. If you’re interested and motivated by mentorship responsibilities, Lenus will support your aspirations.</p>\n<p><strong>Your qualifications as a Senior Web Developer</strong></p>\n<p>Ideally, you are an engineer at heart <a href=\"https://www.notion.so/lenus/Engineers-at-heart-6232f941df4b4b26828c4ca578abb83f\">(click here to read about values, work culture and tech-stack)</a> and possess most of the following skills and personal qualifications:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Have 5 or more years of experience in software development.</li>\n<li>Are an expert in either frontend or backend domain.</li>\n<li>Have a great sense of ownership and experience with taking charge of development projects.</li>\n<li>Have solid written and verbal communication, are able to clearly articulate technically complex problems and solutions to both technical and non-technical colleagues.</li>\n<li>Have experience in working with relational databases like PostgreSQL.</li>\n<li>Attentive to detail with a high focus on writing high quality, maintainable code.</li>\n<li>Are a true believer and a practitioner of automated testing at all levels.</li>\n<li>Are willing to pick up new technologies and frameworks and implement them with the team when required.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Join a diverse engineering team and a growing company</strong></p>\n<p>The people at Lenus work and workout together, they celebrate their achievements together and are connected on a deeper level than just being colleagues. The current team of 10 developers is spread across 4 nationalities. The team is a young, technology-loving, music playing, ramen eating group and they work hard, workout hard, and occasionally, party hard - a social and fun workplace is certainly valued.  You will be able to develop yourself in the direction you prefer. In a growing team, there will be a demand for both a high degree of specialisation as well as a broader perspective of a generalist.</p>\n<p>Lastly, Lenus is financially stable, thanks to fast-growing monthly recurring revenues (currently around 16M DKK/Month) and MtM growth of ca. 10%. Therefore, they are able to offer more than competitive pay to the candidates with the right values and set of competencies.</p>\n<p><strong>About the hiring process</strong></p>\n<p>Kold+Partners is handling the recruiting process. Our process is fast, transparent and tailored to your needs. We are conscious of your time and the fact that you are busy in your daily life. Read more about our approach and your journey as a candidate here.</p>\n<p>If you have any questions regarding the job or Lenus eHealth, feel free to contact Peter Kold on +45 29 89 09 03 or at <a href=\"mailto:peter@koldpartners.com\">peter@koldpartners.com</a> and Valdemar Jørgensen on +45 42 22 72 68 or at <a href=\"mailto:valdemar@koldpartners.com\">valdemar@koldpartners.com</a>.</p>\n",
