      "title": "Senior Frontend Developer",
      "description": "<p>Do you want to build awesome stuff and have fun while doing it? Then come join iPaper frontend team in Aarhus as the new Senior Frontend Developer. iPaper helps businesses convert their catalogues to sales- and marketing tools with the Flipbook and Display products.</p>\n<p><strong>The tech stack</strong></p>\n<p>You’ll work with VueJS, TypeScript, SCSS, Webpack and GIT. It's a great combination of tools that the new product is built on.</p>\n<p><strong>Work with new technologies and a new product</strong></p>\n<p>In short, you will work on a SaaS platform with 65+ million visitors every month. iPaper Displays is the new product. It's the future shopping experience, has plenty of room for new technologies and researching cutting edge stuff - no block-chain, Machine Learning, AI or Quantum Computing. Sorry! As the team in unison proclaims: “We aren't that hip”. It’s expected that you'll pitch in with ideas to develop and improve the product and codebase.</p>\n<p>Flipbooks is the original product, the spine of the company. One of the tasks at hand is converting the last bits of the original JavaScript to TypeScript and upgrading the codebase as you deprecate features and browsers.</p>\n<p>You will have a chance to influence the product moving forward and you can take responsibility of projects that you think are exciting and worth exploring if it’ll benefit the product. It’s a position where you will be able to develop and improve your skills.</p>\n<p><strong>Great benefits, a friendly team and professional development</strong></p>\n<p>The package includes a competitive salary based on your experience and qualifications. The HQ is a very nice and modern office in the heart of Aarhus (parking is possible). At the office, you will be met with a lunch scheme, soda, tea, coffee and snacks and you will be invited to join your colleagues for a drink on Fridays.</p>\n<p>You will join a diverse company of 30 people spread across 10 nationalities. The development team counts 8 people. The company culture is built on giving trust and responsibility to employees, so you won’t spend time on tracking tasks - you won't be registering hours and you’re free to work at your own pace.</p>\n<p><strong>Who are you?</strong></p>\n<p>Your main experience lies with TypeScript or JavaScript, preferably from working on large projects. In addition, you also have worked with HTML &amp; CSS and you have experience with source control - merging, branching, pull requests. You like to participate in code reviews - everything is reviewed and a lot of bugs are caught doing it.</p>\n<p>As a person, you want to influence product development and you want to keep improving your skills to become even better at doing what you do best: coding.</p>\n<p><strong>About the recruitment process</strong></p>\n<p>Kold+Partners are handling the recruiting process. Our process is fast, transparent and tailored to your needs. We are conscious of your time and the fact that you are busy in your daily life. Read more about our approach and your journey as a candidate <a href=\"https://www.koldpartners.com/en/for-candidates/our-approach/\">here</a>. You can read more about iPaper <a href=\"https://www.ipaper.io/\">here</a>.</p>\n<p>If you have any questions regarding the job or iPaper, feel free to contact Peter Kold, Head Recruiter, on +45 29 89 09 03 or at <a href=\"mailto:peter@koldpartners.com\">peter@koldpartners.com</a>.</p>\n",
      "how_to_apply": "<p><a href=\"https://jobs.lever.co/koldpartners/6ba25cc3-2e00-43a5-8ea5-744023486404?lever-origin=applied&amp;lever-source%5B%5D=GitHub\">Click here to apply</a></p>\n",
